sudo apt-get install haskell-platform for installing it
type ghc -o hello hello.hs in terminal to compile
type ./hello to run the compiled file
type ghc -O2 --make A.hs -threaded -rtsopts to compile with -threaded and optimizations on
type time ./A +RTS -N2 to run on on two cores and show the time it took to process the output
type ghci in terminal to open the interpreter for quick scripting
